WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.800
From within an RStudio Cloud workspace, there are four possible roles that an individual

00:00:06.800 --> 00:00:08.560
can occupy.

00:00:08.560 --> 00:00:12.840
As the creator of the workspace, we are given the default status of administrator, and we

00:00:12.840 --> 00:00:16.040
cannot change that status.

00:00:16.040 --> 00:00:19.559
Administrators have full privileges within a workspace.

00:00:19.559 --> 00:00:24.240
Administrators can manage the workspace and all of the projects, including their own,

00:00:24.240 --> 00:00:29.600
and also view all of the projects within a workspace, including private projects.

00:00:30.080 --> 00:00:34.400
Moderators have all of the same privileges as an administrator, except that moderators

00:00:34.400 --> 00:00:38.320
cannot add or remove learners from the workspace.

00:00:38.320 --> 00:00:42.480
This means that moderators can manage all of the projects as well as view all of the

00:00:42.480 --> 00:00:45.560
projects within a workspace.

00:00:45.560 --> 00:00:49.639
Contributors can create and manage their own projects, and they can also view any projects

00:00:49.639 --> 00:00:51.980
that have been shared with them.

00:00:51.980 --> 00:00:56.360
As an administrator or moderator, we can also control whether or not contributors can see

00:00:56.360 --> 00:01:01.360
the names of other members in the workspace, make their projects visible to all members,

00:01:01.360 --> 00:01:04.800
and change project resources.

00:01:04.800 --> 00:01:08.279
Viewers have the most restrictive permissions and can only view projects that have been

00:01:08.279 --> 00:01:12.160
shared with the workspace or with them as an individual.

00:01:12.160 --> 00:01:16.199
As an administrator or moderator, we can also control whether or not a viewer can see

00:01:16.199 --> 00:01:18.559
the names of other members in the workspace.

00:01:26.360 --> 00:01:30.000
For more information, visit www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov

